type FinalPrincipalExchangeCalculation:
    [docReference ISDA FPML version "recordkeeping-5.13"
        provision "Indicates whether the Principal Exchange on the inflation leg is floored or not. If TRUE, Principal Exchange takes the form: Inflation Notional Amount * Max(1, Index Final/ Index Base). If FALSE, the Principal Exchange takes the form: Inflation Notional Amount * Index Final / Index Base. Added for Inflation Asset Swap."]
    [docReference ISDA FPML version "confirmation-5.13"
        provision "Indicates whether the Principal Exchange on the inflation leg is floored or not. If TRUE, Principal Exchange takes the form: Inflation Notional Amount * Max(1, Index Final/ Index Base). If FALSE, the Principal Exchange takes the form: Inflation Notional Amount * Index Final / Index Base. Added for Inflation Asset Swap."]

    floored boolean (0..1)
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "recordkeeping-5.13"
            provision "If TRUE, Principal Exchange takes the form: Inflation Notional Amount * Max(1, Index Final/ Index Base). If FALSE, the Principal Exchange takes the form: Inflation Notional Amount * Index Final / Index Base."]
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "confirmation-5.13"
            provision "If TRUE, Principal Exchange takes the form: Inflation Notional Amount * Max(1, Index Final/ Index Base). If FALSE, the Principal Exchange takes the form: Inflation Notional Amount * Index Final / Index Base."]

type FloatingRateDefinition:
    [docReference ISDA FPML version "recordkeeping-5.13"
        provision "A type defining parameters associated with a floating rate reset. This type forms part of the cashflows representation of a stream."]
    [docReference ISDA FPML version "confirmation-5.13"
        provision "A type defining parameters associated with a floating rate reset. This type forms part of the cashflows representation of a stream."]

    calculatedRate number (0..1)
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "recordkeeping-5.13"
            provision "The final calculated rate for a calculation period after any required averaging of rates A calculated rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05."]
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "confirmation-5.13"
            provision "The final calculated rate for a calculation period after any required averaging of rates A calculated rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05."]
    rateObservation RateObservation (0..*)
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "recordkeeping-5.13"
            provision "The details of a particular rate observation, including the fixing date and observed rate. A list of rate observation elements may be ordered in the document by ascending adjusted fixing date. An FpML document containing an unordered list of rate observations is still regarded as a conformant document."]
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "confirmation-5.13"
            provision "The details of a particular rate observation, including the fixing date and observed rate. A list of rate observation elements may be ordered in the document by ascending adjusted fixing date. An FpML document containing an unordered list of rate observations is still regarded as a conformant document."]
    floatingRateMultiplier number (0..1)
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "recordkeeping-5.13"
            provision "A rate multiplier to apply to the floating rate. The multiplier can be a positive or negative decimal. This element should only be included if the multiplier is not equal to 1 (one)."]
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "confirmation-5.13"
            provision "A rate multiplier to apply to the floating rate. The multiplier can be a positive or negative decimal. This element should only be included if the multiplier is not equal to 1 (one)."]
    spread number (0..1)
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "recordkeeping-5.13"
            provision "The ISDA Spread, if any, which applies for the calculation period. The spread is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. For purposes of determining a calculation period amount, if positive the spread will be added to the floating rate and if negative the spread will be subtracted from the floating rate. A positive 10 basis point (0.1%) spread would be represented as 0.001."]
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "confirmation-5.13"
            provision "The ISDA Spread, if any, which applies for the calculation period. The spread is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. For purposes of determining a calculation period amount, if positive the spread will be added to the floating rate and if negative the spread will be subtracted from the floating rate. A positive 10 basis point (0.1%) spread would be represented as 0.001."]
    capRate Strike (0..*)
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "recordkeeping-5.13"
            provision "The cap rate, if any, which applies to the floating rate for the calculation period. The cap rate (strike) is only required where the floating rate on a swap stream is capped at a certain strike level. The cap rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. A cap rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05."]
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "confirmation-5.13"
            provision "The cap rate, if any, which applies to the floating rate for the calculation period. The cap rate (strike) is only required where the floating rate on a swap stream is capped at a certain strike level. The cap rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. A cap rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05."]
    floorRate Strike (0..*)
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "recordkeeping-5.13"
            provision "The floor rate, if any, which applies to the floating rate for the calculation period. The floor rate (strike) is only required where the floating rate on a swap stream is floored at a certain strike level. The floor rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. The floor rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05."]
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "confirmation-5.13"
            provision "The floor rate, if any, which applies to the floating rate for the calculation period. The floor rate (strike) is only required where the floating rate on a swap stream is floored at a certain strike level. The floor rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. The floor rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05."]

