type SinglePartyOption:
    [docReference ISDA FPML version "recordkeeping-5.13"
        provision "A type describing the buyer and seller of an option."]
    [docReference ISDA FPML version "confirmation-5.13"
        provision "A type describing the buyer and seller of an option."]

    buyerPartyReference PartyReference (1..1)
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "recordkeeping-5.13"
            provision "A reference to the party that buys this instrument, ie. pays for this instrument and receives the rights defined by it. See 2000 ISDA definitions Article 11.1 (b). In the case of FRAs this the fixed rate payer."]
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "confirmation-5.13"
            provision "A reference to the party that buys this instrument, ie. pays for this instrument and receives the rights defined by it. See 2000 ISDA definitions Article 11.1 (b). In the case of FRAs this the fixed rate payer."]
    buyerAccountReference AccountReference (0..1)
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "recordkeeping-5.13"
            provision "A reference to the account that buys this instrument."]
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "confirmation-5.13"
            provision "A reference to the account that buys this instrument."]
    sellerPartyReference PartyReference (1..1)
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "recordkeeping-5.13"
            provision "A reference to the party that sells (\"writes\") this instrument, i.e. that grants the rights defined by this instrument and in return receives a payment for it. See 2000 ISDA definitions Article 11.1 (a). In the case of FRAs this is the floating rate payer."]
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "confirmation-5.13"
            provision "A reference to the party that sells (\"writes\") this instrument, i.e. that grants the rights defined by this instrument and in return receives a payment for it. See 2000 ISDA definitions Article 11.1 (a). In the case of FRAs this is the floating rate payer."]
    sellerAccountReference AccountReference (0..1)
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "recordkeeping-5.13"
            provision "A reference to the account that sells this instrument."]
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "confirmation-5.13"
            provision "A reference to the account that sells this instrument."]

type StubCalculationPeriodAmount:
    [docReference ISDA FPML version "recordkeeping-5.13"
        provision "A type defining how the initial or final stub calculation period amounts is calculated. For example, the rate to be applied to the initial or final stub calculation period may be the linear interpolation of two different tenors for the floating rate index specified in the calculation period amount component, e.g. A two month stub period may used the linear interpolation of a one month and three month floating rate. The different rate tenors would be specified in this component. Note that a maximum of two rate tenors can be specified. If a stub period uses a single index tenor and this is the same as that specified in the calculation period amount component then the initial stub or final stub component, as the case may be, must not be included."]
    [docReference ISDA FPML version "confirmation-5.13"
        provision "A type defining how the initial or final stub calculation period amounts is calculated. For example, the rate to be applied to the initial or final stub calculation period may be the linear interpolation of two different tenors for the floating rate index specified in the calculation period amount component, e.g. A two month stub period may used the linear interpolation of a one month and three month floating rate. The different rate tenors would be specified in this component. Note that a maximum of two rate tenors can be specified. If a stub period uses a single index tenor and this is the same as that specified in the calculation period amount component then the initial stub or final stub component, as the case may be, must not be included."]

    calculationPeriodDatesReference CalculationPeriodDatesReference (0..1)
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "recordkeeping-5.13"
            provision "A pointer style reference to the associated calculation period dates component defined elsewhere in the document."]
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "confirmation-5.13"
            provision "A pointer style reference to the associated calculation period dates component defined elsewhere in the document."]
    initialStub StubValue (0..1)
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "recordkeeping-5.13"
            provision "Specifies how the initial stub amount is calculated. A single floating rate tenor different to that used for the regular part of the calculation periods schedule may be specified, or two floating tenors may be specified. If two floating rate tenors are specified then Linear Interpolation (in accordance with the 2000 ISDA Definitions, Section 8.3. Interpolation) is assumed to apply. Alternatively, an actual known stub rate or stub amount may be specified."]
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "confirmation-5.13"
            provision "Specifies how the initial stub amount is calculated. A single floating rate tenor different to that used for the regular part of the calculation periods schedule may be specified, or two floating tenors may be specified. If two floating rate tenors are specified then Linear Interpolation (in accordance with the 2000 ISDA Definitions, Section 8.3. Interpolation) is assumed to apply. Alternatively, an actual known stub rate or stub amount may be specified."]
    finalStub StubValue (0..1)
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "recordkeeping-5.13"
            provision "Specifies how the final stub amount is calculated. A single floating rate tenor different to that used for the regular part of the calculation periods schedule may be specified, or two floating tenors may be specified. If two floating rate tenors are specified then Linear Interpolation (in accordance with the 2000 ISDA Definitions, Section 8.3. Interpolation) is assumed to apply. Alternatively, an actual known stub rate or stub amount may be specified."]
        [docReference ISDA FPML version "confirmation-5.13"
            provision "Specifies how the final stub amount is calculated. A single floating rate tenor different to that used for the regular part of the calculation periods schedule may be specified, or two floating tenors may be specified. If two floating rate tenors are specified then Linear Interpolation (in accordance with the 2000 ISDA Definitions, Section 8.3. Interpolation) is assumed to apply. Alternatively, an actual known stub rate or stub amount may be specified."]

